            ["Mnemonic for Page 24 - Item 1", "Mnemonic for Page 24 - Item 2", "Mnemonic for Page 24 - Item 3"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 25 - Item 1"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 26 - Item 1"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 27 - Item 1", "Mnemonic for Page 27 - Item 2"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 28 - Item 1"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 29 - Item 1", "Mnemonic for Page 29 - Item 2"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 30 - Item 1"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 31 - Item 1"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 32 - Item 1", "Mnemonic for Page 32 - Item 2"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 33 - Item 1"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 34 - Item 1", "Mnemonic for Page 34 - Item 2", "Mnemonic for Page 34 - Item 3"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 35 - Item 1"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 36 - Item 1"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 37 - Item 1", "Mnemonic for Page 37 - Item 2"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 38 - Item 1"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 39 - Item 1", "Mnemonic for Page 39 - Item 2"],
            ["Mnemonic for Page 40 - Item 1"], // End of Section 2
            ["Mnemonic for Page 41 - Item 1", "Mnemonic for Page 41 - Item 2"],
            ["A vivid mnemonic for an important fact on Page 42.", "Remember this concept easily with a catchy phrase on Page 42."],
            ["Mnemonic covering the main idea of Page 43."],
            ["Complex idea simplification for Page 44.", "Secondary point mnemonic on Page 44."],
            ['üí° The **diencephalon** includes the **thalamus**, **hypothalamus**, **epithalamus**, and **subthalamus**.', 'üî¨ The cavity of the diencephalon is the **3rd ventricle**.', 'üí° The diencephalon is divided by the **hypothalamic sulcus**.', 'üî¨ The **dorsal part** of the diencephalon includes the Thalamus, Metathalamus (**MGB** & **LGB**), and Epithalamus (**pineal body**, habenular nuclei, posterior commissure).', 'üî¨ The **ventral part** of the diencephalon includes the **Hypothalamus** and **Subthalamus**.', 'üí° The **thalamus** is an oval mass of **grey matter** and functions as a **gateway for the cerebral cortex**.', '‚ùó The thalamus relays **all sensations except smell**.', 'üí° The **diencephalon** includes the **thalamus**, **hypothalamus**, **epithalamus**, and **subthalamus**.', 'üî¨ The cavity of the diencephalon is the **3rd ventricle**.', 'üí° The diencephalon is divided by the **hypothalamic sulcus**.', 'üî¨ The **dorsal part** of the diencephalon includes the Thalamus, Metathalamus (**MGB** & **LGB**), and Epithalamus (**pineal body**, habenular nuclei, posterior commissure).', 'üî¨ The **ventral part** of the diencephalon includes the **Hypothalamus** and **Subthalamus**.', 'üí° The **thalamus** is an oval mass of **grey matter** and functions as a **gateway for the cerebral cortex**.', '‚ùó The thalamus relays **all sensations except smell**.', 'üí° The thalamus also relays **motor** and **limbic impulses** to the cerebral cortex.', 'üî¨ The **anterior end** of the thalamus lies posterior to the **interventricular foramen of Monro**.', 'üî¨ The **posterior end** of the thalamus expands to form the **pulvinar**.', 'üî¨ The **superior surface** of the thalamus is related to the **choroid plexus** and forms part of the floor of the **lateral ventricle**.', 'üî¨ The **inferior surface** of the thalamus is separated from the hypothalamus by the **hypothalamic sulcus** and shows the medial & lateral geniculate bodies po